HEADWORD: Brougham
<hw>Brough"am</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A light, enclosed
carriage, with seats inside for two or four, and the fore wheels so
arranged as to turn short.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

